  <objective>The project proposal addresses the critical need to enhance Moldova's integration into the European Research Area and maximize participation in Horizon Europe. 
As an Associated Country, Moldova faces significant structural challenges in its R&amp;I ecosystem despite its promising foundations and EU association status.
This project will systematically strengthen the operational capacity and professional expertise of Moldova's Horizon Europe Office and NCPs network through five specific objectives: (1) enhancing institutional capacity and operational efficiency; (2) improving proposal development skills and success rates; (3) fostering strategic international research partnerships; (4) increasing awareness of Horizon Europe opportunities; and (5) establishing robust monitoring and sustainability mechanisms.
The methodology employs a strategic framework emphasizing quality-driven implementation, digital-first approaches, decentralization of services, complementarity with existing initiatives, localization of support, and institutionalization of best practices. Implementation follows a structured progression through interconnected work packages focusing on a Business Process Management System development, human resources capacity building, support services delivery, communication and dissemination, and effective project management.
Expected outcomes directly address the call requirements: a strengthened and professionalized NCP system providing consistent, high-quality support services; harmonized practices aligned with EU standards; enhanced capacity of researchers; and increased participation rates. Long-term impacts include advanced ERA integration, reduced R&amp;I divides and support for Moldova's broader European integration aspirations.</objective>
